      • isIccResultsPurifyEnabled

        public boolean isIccResultsPurifyEnabled()
        Gets whether the ICC results shall be purified after the data flow computation. Purification means that flows inside components are dropped if the same flow is also part of an inter-component flow.
        Returns:
        True if the ICC results shall be purified, otherwise false. Note that this method also returns false if ICC processing is disabled.
